“traffic” includes micromobility vehicles, motor vehicles, tram cars, 
vehicles  of  every  description,  pedestrians,  processions,  bodies  of 
police or troops and all animals being ridden, driven or led;

“traffic  signs”  includes  all  signals,  warning  sign  posts,  direction 
posts, signs, marks or devices erected or provided on or near a road 
for the information, guidance or direction of persons using the road;

“vehicle” means a structure capable of moving or being moved or 
used for the conveyance of any person or thing and which maintains 
contact with the ground when in motion;

“weighing machine” includes a portable weighing machine, a static 
weighing machine and a computerized or electronic weigh in-motion 
